<br>
With this patch we introduced the ability for intelligence casters (Enchanters, Magicians, Necromancers and Wizards) to create additional spell scrolls using their research skill. Many of the newly researchable spells have only been available from quests or killing NPCs in the past. The new research still requires components from risky locations or dangerous foes. Our goal is to increase the number of ways to earn rare spells, without reducing the challenge required. <br>
<br>
This, however, creates a bit of an inequity between the intelligence casters and the priest classes (Clerics, Druids and Shaman) when it comes to acquiring this type of spell. While there is nothing inherently wrong with different classes earning their spells in different ways, we don't see a reason to give more options to one type of caster than another. In this case, we have taken the opportunity to give the research skill a little more value and at the same time negate any imbalance between classes. <br>
<br>
Some time in the near future we plan to introduce recipes for the creation of certain spells for the priest classes. Intelligence casters can use their research skill to create these priest spell scrolls, and priest classes will benefit by having an alternate method for obtaining these spells. This helps out both priests and intelligence casters, and creates a new niche for research as a trade skill. <br>
<br>
Alan <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Specifically: <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> While there is nothing inherently wrong with different classes earning their spells in different ways, we don't see a reason to give more options to one type of caster than another. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My problem with this statment is simple.  EQ+RoK+SoV+SoL+PoP<br>
<br>
Int casters obtain spells-buying, research, loot<br>
<br>
Wis caster obtain spells-buying, loot<br>
<br>
Now all the sudden, they don't feel it's fair for some to have more options for obtaining spells than others?  Golly a cleric could walk up to a vendor and buy their spells, or loot the &quot;rare&quot; ones.  Wizzards, had to buy, loot and simply collect a few runes (which are easily found on various vendors).  Mages had to buy, loot and run all across the land to get stupid drops to research theirs, sure we could buy the words (or even loot them), but then ya had to stop xp'ing and run for an hour to camp some greeny for 20 minutes to get you 1 chance to combine, ohhhh you failed, another 20 minutes getting that crap drop, hope you brought more than one word with you, and more than one of every other component needed, so that you can sit there and camp this greeny for 20+ minutes for each attempt.<br>
<br>
But, ohhhhhhh how unfair it is to expect priest class' to only have 2 options.  WTF wizzrds/necro's/chanters only had 3, we had 3 but 1 involved killing that green shark (etc etc etc) for hours on end, not xp'ing.<br>
<br>
/boogle kill xp mob hoping for a spell to drop, words to drop, runes to drop-vs-killing greenies for hours to get enough shark fins to actually suceed in researching a spell......<br>
<br>
Yeah, priests would be severely crippled if they were expected to buy/loot spells.<br>
<br>
I don't complain for me, I complain for the younger mages.  Soooo glad to see that I'll be able to make the &quot;rarer&quot; priest spells for them now that the prices for these spells are 5pp.<br>
<br>
Maybe, they should revamp mage research so it's more inline with wizzard/necro/chanter research, BEFORE they allow us to make priest spells (and give the priests the old mage pharm xxxxx greenie system)<br>
<br>
